This paper discusses the use of a specific R package for analyzing and visualizing data related to research publications, which falls under the broad category of digital libraries (cs.DL). The paper also mentions the use of Web of Science (WoS) downloads, which suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and potentially also on citation analysis (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper may touch on issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and social networks (cs.SI) given the potential implications of using different metrics for assessing researchers.
